---
import Page from '../../layouts/Page.astro'
---
<Page
  title="Features"
  label="Product"
  hero="Everything your community needs"
  sub="Built from the ground up for real communities — not repurposed enterprise software."
  description="Explore all the features Krenla offers: real-time messaging, voice rooms, discovery, threads, and more."
>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M4 5h12M4 10h8M4 15h10" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Real-time messaging</h3>
      <p>Messages delivered instantly with read receipts, typing indicators, reactions, and threaded replies. Every conversation feels alive.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="7" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.6"/><path d="M10 6v4l3 2" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Community spaces</h3>
      <p>Create organized communities with channels, roles, and granular permissions. Scale from a small group to hundreds of thousands without friction.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M3 4h14v9H10l-5 3V13H3V4Z" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Discussion threads</h3>
      <p>Long-form discussions that don't get lost in chat. Upvotes, nested replies, pinning, and smart sorting keep the best content visible.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 3a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v3a4 4 0 0 1-8 0V7a4 4 0 0 1 4-4Z" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.6"/><path d="M5 10a5 5 0 0 0 10 0M10 15v2" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Voice & video rooms</h3>
      <p>Crystal-clear audio and video with noise cancellation, screen sharing, and stage mode for presentations. No account linking required.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 4l1.8 3.6L16 8.5l-3 2.9.7 4.1L10 13.4l-3.7 2.1.7-4.1-3-2.9 4.2-.9L10 4Z" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Smart discovery</h3>
      <p>A feed built around your interests, not engagement bait. Krenla surfaces communities and conversations you'll actually want to be part of.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><rect x="4" y="3" width="12" height="15" rx="2" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.6"/><path d="M7 8h6M7 11h4" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Privacy & security</h3>
      <p>End-to-end encryption on direct messages, granular privacy controls, two-factor authentication, and zero data selling. Your conversations are yours.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Built differently</h2>
    <p>Most platforms start as chat tools and bolt on community features later. Krenla was designed from the beginning as a unified space where messaging, structured discussion, and discovery all reinforce each other.</p>
    <p>When someone asks a question in a channel, it can become a thread. When a thread gets traction, it surfaces in discovery. When someone finds it through discovery, they join the community. That loop is intentional — and it's what makes communities on Krenla grow organically.</p>

    <h2>Roles & permissions</h2>
    <p>Community owners can define unlimited custom roles with fine-grained permissions: who can post, who can moderate, who can invite, who can access private channels. Built for communities of every size and structure.</p>

    <h2>Integrations</h2>
    <p>Krenla connects with the tools your community already uses — GitHub, Notion, Google Calendar, and more. Webhooks and a public API let developers build custom integrations for anything else.</p>
  </div>
</Page>
